the deal announced tuesday would provide $46 in cash and junior securities with a face value of $6.50 for each share
in december, the group led by chairman samuel j. heyman had offered $1.35 billion, or $40 in cash and $8.50 in securities per share
a bidding war has erupted for textile giant j.p. stevens &amp; co. with rival west point-pepperell inc. offering to buy the company for about $867 million in cash and a management-led group jumping its cash and securities offer to about $850 million
stevens also said tuesday it had received a third, unidentified offer
the management group headed by chairman whitney stevens has offered to pay $40 in cash and $15 in securities for each of the company's 15.5 million common shares outstanding in a leveraged buyout. west point-pepperell offered $56 a share in cash under a negotiated merger agreement
